{# templates/roadmaps/forex/developing-trading-strategy.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('forex_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('forex_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- article hero – forex style -->
        <div class="article-hero animate">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>Developing a Simple <span>Trading Strategy</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    A trading strategy is your roadmap to consistent profits. Learn how to combine entry rules, exit rules,
                    and risk management into a repeatable plan that you can backtest and trust.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 4: Skill Building · 10 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">🧩 What Makes a Trading Strategy?</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                A trading strategy is a set of objective rules that tells you exactly when to enter, when to exit,
                and how much to risk. It removes emotion from the equation and allows you to evaluate your performance
                based on data, not feelings.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--gray-color);">
                In this article, you’ll learn the essential components of any strategy – entry triggers, stop loss placement,
                take profit targets, and position sizing. Then we’ll walk through building a simple moving average crossover
                strategy that you can test on a demo account.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- key components grid -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-sign-in-alt"></i> Entry Rules</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">When to buy/sell</div>
                <p>Based on technical indicators (e.g., moving average crossover, RSI oversold) or price action (e.g., breakout of resistance). Must be specific and unambiguous.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-sign-out-alt"></i> Exit Rules</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">When to close</div>
                <p>Includes stop loss (where you're wrong) and take profit (where you're right). Can also be trailing stops or time‑based exits.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i> Risk Management</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">Position sizing</div>
                <p>How much of your account to risk per trade (usually 1‑2%). Determines lot size based on stop distance.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Market Conditions</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">When to trade</div>
                <p>Some strategies work only in trending markets, others in ranges. Define the environment that suits your strategy.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- deeper dive: building a simple strategy -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">🔨 Building a Moving Average Crossover Strategy</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
                Let’s create a simple trend‑following strategy using two exponential moving averages (EMA).
            </p>
            <div style="background: #f1f5f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 16px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--forex-color); margin-right: 10px;"></i> <strong>Indicators:</strong> 10‑period EMA (fast) and 30‑period EMA (slow) on 1‑hour chart.</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--forex-color); margin-right: 10px;"></i> <strong>Entry (long):</strong> When fast EMA crosses above slow EMA.</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--forex-color); margin-right: 10px;"></i> <strong>Entry (short):</strong> When fast EMA crosses below slow EMA.</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--forex-color); margin-right: 10px;"></i> <strong>Stop loss:</strong> 20 pips below the recent swing low (for long) or above swing high (for short).</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--forex-color); margin-right: 10px;"></i> <strong>Take profit:</strong> 60 pips (1:3 risk‑reward), or when fast EMA crosses back.</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--forex-color); margin-right: 10px;"></i> <strong>Risk per trade:</strong> 1% of account.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px; background-color: #eef2ff; border-left-color: #3182ce;"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Always backtest your strategy on historical data before trading it live. Many platforms allow you to run a backtest in minutes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- INTERACTIVE TOOL: Strategy Builder Simulator -->
        <div class="card animate" style="margin: 40px 0;" id="strategy-builder">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-wrench"></i> Strategy Builder Simulator</h3>
            <p>Combine basic building blocks to see a description of your custom strategy.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 15px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">Entry Condition</label>
                    <select id="entryCondition" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%;">
                        <option value="macrossover">Moving Average Crossover</option>
                        <option value="rsioverbought">RSI Oversold (&lt;30) for long</option>
                        <option value="rsioversold">RSI Overbought (&gt;70) for short</option>
                        <option value="supportbounce">Bounce from Support</option>
                        <option value="resistancebreak">Breakout above Resistance</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">Stop Loss Placement</label>
                    <select id="stopPlacement" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%;">
                        <option value="swing">Below recent swing low / above swing high</option>
                        <option value="atr">1.5x ATR</option>
                        <option value="fixed">Fixed 30 pips</option>
                        <option value="ema">Below fast EMA</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">Take Profit Method</label>
                    <select id="tpMethod" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%;">
                        <option value="rr2">Fixed 1:2 risk‑reward</option>
                        <option value="rr3">Fixed 1:3 risk‑reward</option>
                        <option value="resistance">Previous resistance/support</option>
                        <option value="ema">Fast EMA cross</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 0 0 auto; align-self: flex-end;">
                    <button id="strategyBuildBtn" class="btn-outline" style="padding: 12px 30px;">Build Strategy</button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="strategyPreview" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 15px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem;">
                Your custom strategy description will appear here.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- example trade box -->
        <div class="highlight-box animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> Example – EMA Crossover Trade</h3>
            <p>On the 1‑hour chart of EUR/USD, the 10 EMA crosses above the 30 EMA at 1.1050. You check that the overall trend is up (price above both EMAs). You enter long at 1.1050, place a stop loss at 1.1020 (30 pips below the last swing low), and set a take profit at 1.1140 (1:3 ratio, 90 pips). The trade hits your target two days later.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- pro tip: simplicity wins -->
        <div class="pro-tip animate" style="background-color: #fff5f0; border-left-color: #ff6b35;">
            <h4 style="margin-top: 0;"><i class="fas fa-dragon" style="color:#ff6b35;"></i> Keep It Simple</h4>
            <p>Many beginners add too many indicators, leading to analysis paralysis. A simple strategy with 2‑3 rules, properly backtested, often outperforms a complex one. <strong>Master the basics before adding complexity.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- quiz section (conditional) -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: page.journey.name, slug: slug, retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #ff6b35; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test your knowledge: Trading Strategy Basics</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What are the three essential components of any trading strategy?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Indicators, charts, news</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Entry rules, exit rules, risk management</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Leverage, margin, broker</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Fear, greed, hope</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. A moving average crossover (fast above slow) typically signals:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">A potential uptrend / buy signal</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">A potential downtrend / sell signal</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Range‑bound market</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">High volatility</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. Why is it important to backtest a strategy?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To impress other traders</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">To see how it would have performed historically and validate its profitability</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To guarantee future profits</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To find the best broker</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. What is the recommended risk per trade for a beginner?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">1‑2% of account balance</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">10‑20%</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">50%</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">As much as possible</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. What is a common pitfall when building a strategy?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Using too few indicators</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Over‑optimizing (curve‑fitting) to past data</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Testing on a demo</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Keeping a trading journal</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- next steps in phase 4 (skill building) -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue building your skills</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'forex', slug: 'fundamental-analysis-central-banks' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-university"></i>
                    <h3>Fundamental Analysis</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--gray-color);">Central banks and economic data.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'forex', slug: 'advanced-risk-management' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-link"></i>
                    <h3>Advanced Risk Management</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--gray-color);">Hedging and correlations.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'forex', slug: 'demo-to-live' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-rocket"></i>
                    <h3>From Demo to Live</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--gray-color);">When and how to transition.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
